// Development signing for the generated Xcode project.
//
// Why this file exists: an ad-hoc signature's designated requirement pins the
// exact cdhash, which changes on every build. macOS TCC stores that requirement
// when you grant Accessibility or microphone access, so each rebuild invalidates
// the grant and the app is re-prompted on every paste, while the stale entry
// still appears (enabled) in System Settings. Signing with a certificate
// identity keeps the requirement stable across rebuilds, so the grants stick.
//
// The defaults below are ad-hoc so that a checkout without a signing
// certificate still builds. scripts/generate-xcodeproj.sh detects an
// "Apple Development" identity and writes Local.xcconfig with it, which is
// included last and wins. Local.xcconfig is not tracked: it holds a
// machine-specific team ID.
//
// Releases are signed with Developer ID by bundle.sh, not from here.

CODE_SIGN_STYLE = Manual
CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = -

#include? "Local.xcconfig"
